# Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS

## Project paths

- App Router lives in `src/app` — never create a root-level `app/` directory
- Route-specific components: colocate in the route folder under `src/app`
- Shared components: `src/components`
- Hooks: `src/hooks`
- Utilities and helpers: `src/lib`

## TypeScript

- Use TypeScript for all new code; prefer interfaces for object shapes
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` with narrowing or Zod validation
- Use functional components with explicit prop interfaces
- Favor named exports for components and utilities

## Tailwind CSS

- Use Tailwind utility classes for layout and styling
- Mobile-first responsive design (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints)
- Keep class lists readable; extract repeated patterns to components
- Use design tokens / theme variables when the project defines them

## Next.js conventions

- Default to Server Components; add `'use client'` only when needed
- Use the App Router — not the Pages Router
- Use `next/image` for images with explicit width/height or fill
- Use route handlers (`route.ts`) for API endpoints under `src/app/api`
- Implement `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` for data-fetching routes

## Code quality

- Follow existing ESLint and Prettier configuration
- Match surrounding file structure and naming conventions
- Validate user inputs; handle errors with clear UI feedback
- Minimize comments; prefer clear names over explanatory noise

